Lastly, you can also provide categorical or discrete data to be colored.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# provide type = "discrete"
mtcars %>%
  head() %>%
  gt() %>%
  gt_color_rows(
    cyl, 
    palette = "ggthemes::colorblind", 
    # note that you can manually define range like c(4, 6, 8)
    domain = range(mtcars$cyl),
    pal_type = "discrete"
   )
```

