### `gt_sparkline()`

A typical sparkline for your table!


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mtcars %>%
   dplyr::group_by(cyl) %>%
   # must end up with list of data for each row in the input dataframe
   dplyr::summarize(mpg_data = list(mpg), .groups = "drop") %>%
   gt() %>%
   gt_plt_sparkline(mpg_data)
```

